Importing data 

library(readr)

chats = read_csv("data/chat.csv", col_names = c("time","device_id","login",
                                                "channel","country","player",
                                                "game"))
streams = read_csv("data/stream.csv")

Short-term demand evolution of most popular games 

library(lubridate)
library(dplyr)
library(highcharter)
library(ggplot2)

stream_evo = streams %>%
  select('time','game') %>% 
  mutate(time = as.numeric(as.POSIXct(time))) %>% 
  mutate(cuts = cut(time, c(1420070200,
                            1420075346,
                            1420080293,
                            1420085239,
                            1420090186,
                            1420095132,
                            1420100079,
                            1420105025,
                            1420109972,
                            1420114918,
                            1420119865,
                            1420124811,
                            1420129758,
                            1420134704,
                            1420139651,
                            1420144597,
                            1420149544,
                            1420154490,
                            1420159437,
                            1420164383,
                            1420169330,
                            Inf))) %>% 
  group_by(game, cuts) %>% 
  summarize(n = n()) %>% 
  mutate(popularity = sum(n), time = as.numeric( 
    sub("[^,]*,([^]]*)\\]", "\\1", cuts)), 
    time = as.POSIXct(time, origin = "1970-01-01", tz = "GMT")) %>% 
  filter(popularity > 10000)

ggplot(data=stream_evo, aes(x= time, y=n, colour=game)) + geom_smooth(se=FALSE) +
  ggtitle("Trend of most popular games in one day") + 
  xlab("Date and Time") +
  ylab("Number of viewers")

stream_evo_cntry = streams %>%

  mutate(time = as.numeric(as.POSIXct(time))) %>% 
  mutate(cuts = cut(time, c(1420070200,
                            1420075346,
                            1420080293,
                            1420085239,
                            1420090186,
                            1420095132,
                            1420100079,
                            1420105025,
                            1420109972,
                            1420114918,
                            1420119865,
                            1420124811,
                            1420129758,
                            1420134704,
                            1420139651,
                            1420144597,
                            1420149544,
                            1420154490,
                            1420159437,
                            1420164383,
                            1420169330,
                            Inf))) %>% 
  group_by(game, country, cuts) %>% 
  summarize(n = n()) %>% 
  mutate(popularity = sum(n), time = as.numeric( 
    sub("[^,]*,([^]]*)\\]", "\\1", cuts)),

Anonymous viewers vs.Â subscribers (Streamers perspective) 

anms_scbr = streams %>% 
  group_by(subscriber) %>% 
  summarize(n = n()) %>% 
  na.omit() %>% 
  mutate(n = n*100/sum(n)) 
  
anms_scbr %>% hchart(type='pie', hcaes(x=subscriber, y=n), name='%') %>% hc_xAxis(title=list(text='Is the user subscried to streamer?'))
anms_scbr_hist = streams %>% 
  group_by(channel, subscriber) %>% 
  na.omit() %>% 
  summarize(total = n()) %>% 
  mutate(t_tf = sum(total))

ggplot(anms_scbr_hist, aes(x=reorder(channel, total), y=total, fill=subscriber)) +
  geom_col() +
  ggtitle("Subscribers vs. Anonymous in most popular streamers") + 
  xlab("Streamer Name") +
  ylab("Number of viewers")

anms_scbr_hist_t = anms_scbr_hist %>% 
  filter(subscriber == 'true')
cor.test(anms_scbr_hist_t$total, anms_scbr_hist_t$t_tf)
